# git clone .....


1-helm repo add grafana https://grafana.github.io/helm-charts
2-helm repo update
3-helm install grafana stable/grafana

4- helm list
	: grafana and prometheus deployed


5-kubectl get all
  should see everything


6- kubectl expose service grafana --type=NodePort --target-port=3000 --name=grafana-ext
	answer is service/grafana-ext exposed

7- kubectl get svs

	grafana-ext is exposed

8- access grafana
	minikube service grafana-ext
	 copy and paste to check in browser

9- kubectl get secret --namespace default grafana -o yaml

  you should be able see the admin password and user name encripted

10- command to decript the user name :


           Type the encripte info
 	echo "encripte_user=" | openssl base64 -d ; echo 

 	same for password same command

 11- or use the same command : kubectl get secret --namespace default grafana -o jsonpath="{.data.admin-password}" | base64 --decode ; echo


 12-import dashboard code 6417
